sql_query.sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM (SELECT 1 AS one FROM "categories" WHERE ((FALSE AND LENGTH(COALESCE(email_in, '')) > 0 AND email_in_allow_strangers)
          OR categories.id NOT IN (SELECT category_id FROM category_groups)
          OR categories.id IN (
                SELECT category_id
                  FROM category_groups
                 WHERE permission_type IN (1)
                   AND (group_id = 0 OR group_id IN (SELECT group_id FROM group_users WHERE user_id = 1678))
             )) LIMIT 1) subquery_for_count

sql_query.sql:
SELECT "groups"."id", "groups"."name" FROM "groups" INNER JOIN "group_users" ON "groups"."id" = "group_users"."group_id" WHERE "group_users"."user_id" = 1678 AND (groups.id > 0) AND ( groups.id IN (
   SELECT id
     FROM groups
    WHERE visibility_level = 0

   UNION ALL

   SELECT id
     FROM groups
    WHERE visibility_level = 1
      AND 1678 IS NOT NULL

   UNION ALL

   SELECT g.id
     FROM groups g
     JOIN group_users gu ON gu.group_id = g.id AND gu.user_id = 1678
    WHERE g.visibility_level = 2

   UNION ALL

   SELECT g.id
     FROM groups g
LEFT JOIN group_users gu ON gu.group_id = g.id AND gu.user_id = 1678 AND gu.owner
    WHERE g.visibility_level = 3
      AND (gu.id IS NOT NULL OR FALSE)

   UNION ALL

   SELECT g.id
     FROM groups g
     JOIN group_users gu ON gu.group_id = g.id AND gu.user_id = 1678 AND gu.owner
    WHERE g.visibility_level = 4
 )
) ORDER BY name ASC
